    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "that's a good start. i noticed u mentioned Lochner v. New York though—some people argue that using substantive due process to strike down economic regulations like that was actually a misuse of the doctrine. would u say that the 'procedural' side of due process—basically just making sure the government follows the right rules and steps—is less important than the 'substantive' side you just described?",
