      "role": "user",
      "content": "interesting. so u think the court's job is mostly to prioritize these substantive rights over the procedural rules? i've heard some legal scholars argue that the whole idea of 'substantive due process' is actually pretty dangerous because it lets judges basically make up new rights that aren't explicitly in the constitution, which they say undermines the democratic process. how do u respond to that critique?",
